cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image and video understanding using deep convolutional networks, specifically for action recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of support-vector-machines (SVM) and deep neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with video quality and camera viewpoints, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of hand-crafted features, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
